res where one of the Anglo Sikh war happened. The Ground floor of the memorial is 2 meters above the surrounding area.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /> The monument has collections of murals, portraits and paintings depicting battlefield made by renowned painters Jaswant Singh and Kirpal Singh.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cityairnews.com/content/hardly-any-visitor-historical-anglo-sikh-war-memorial-ferozeshah|title=Hardly any visitor for historical Anglo Sikh War Memorial at Ferozeshah | date=1 March 2015 | first=Vikramditya | last=Sharma | publisher=City Air News|access-date=30 December 2018}}</ref> The bronze carved quotes on Cunningham's history; the wars of Shah Mohammad; the Anglo Sikh war weapons donated by the Punjab Gvernment from the Patiyala Museum, is displayed in the Memorial.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://ferozepur.nic.in/tourist-place/anglo-sikh-war-memorial-ferozeshah/ ferozepur.nic.in]\n*[http://punjabtourism.gov.in/Punjab.html#/attraction/79/anglo-sikh-war-memorial punjabtourism. org]\n\n[[Category:Monuments and memorials]]\n[[Category:Monuments and memorials in Punjab, India]]\n[[Category:Museums in Punjab, India]]\n", "name_user": "Certes", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fix links to Punjab (viaWP:JWB)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anglo_Sikh_War_Memorial"}
